functions.label: downloadFileAs
description:
Convenient method to use for a single file download
**Note**: for multiple files use the downloadMultipleAs method, do not iterate with this method here

children.label: filename
description: full name of the file

children.label: payload
description: either a Blob content, or a Record with a stringified content and type

returnComment: a Promise that resolves when the download has been correctly started

functions.label: downloadMultipleAs
description: Multiple files download method

children.label: files
description:
a Record containing one entry per file: the key entry should be the filename
and the value either a Blob content, or a Record with a stringified content and type

returnComment: a Promise that resolves when all the downloads have been correctly started

interfaces.label: KibanaLocation
description:
This interface represents a location in Kibana to which one can navigate
using the `core.application.navigateToApp()` method.

children.label: app
description: Kibana application ID.

children.label: path
description: A relative URL path within a Kibana application.

children.label: state
description:
A serializable location state object, which the app can use to determine
what should be displayed on the screen.

interfaces.label: LocatorDefinition
description: A convenience interface used to define and register a locator.

children.label: id
description: Unique ID of the locator. Should be constant and unique across Kibana.

children.label: getLocation
description:
Returns a deep link, including location state, which can be used for
navigation in Kibana.

children.label: params
description: Parameters from which to generate a Kibana location.

interfaces.label: LocatorPublic
description: Public interface of a registered locator.

children.label: getLocation
description: Returns a reference to a Kibana client-side location.

children.label: params
description: URL locator parameters.

children.label: getUrl
description:
Returns a URL as a string.

You may want to use `getRedirectUrl` instead. `getRedirectUrl` will
preserve the location state, whereas the `getUrl` just returns the URL
without the location state. Use this method if you know you don't need
remember the location state and version of the URL locator.

children.label: params
description: URL locator parameters.

children.label: getUrlParams
description: URL construction parameters.

children.label: getRedirectUrl
description:
Returns a URL to the redirect endpoint, which will redirect the user to
the final destination.

children.label: params
description: URL locator parameters.

children.label: options
description: URL serialization options.

children.label: navigate
description:
Navigate using the `core.application.navigateToApp()` method to a Kibana
location generated by this locator. This method is available only on the
browser.

children.label: params
description: URL locator parameters.

children.label: navigationParams
description: Navigation parameters.

children.label: navigateSync
description:
Synchronous fire-and-forget navigation method. Use it when you want to
navigate without waiting for the navigation to complete and you don't
care to process any async promise errors.

children.label: params
description: URL locator parameters.

children.label: navigationParams
description: Navigation parameters.

children.label: useUrl
description:
React hook which returns a URL string given locator parameters. Returns
empty string if URL is being loaded or an error happened.

children.label: id
description: Locator ID.

children.label: version
description: Kibana version when locator params were generated.

children.label: params
description: Locator params.

children.label: objectType
description: The type of the object to share. for example lens, dashboard, etc.

children.label: objectTypeAlias
description: An alias of type of the object to share, that's more human friendly.

children.label: objectTypeMeta
description: Allows for passing contextual information that each consumer can provide to customize the share menu

children.label: objectId

children.label: shareableUrl
description:
Current url for sharing. This can be set in cases where `window.location.href`
does not contain a shareable URL (e.g. if using session storage to store the current
app state is enabled). In these cases the property should contain the URL in a
format which makes it possible to use it without having access to any other state
like the current session.

If not set it will default to `window.location.href`

interfaces.label: AnonymousAccessServiceContract
description:
The contract that is used to check anonymous access for the purposes of sharing public links. The implementation is intended to be
provided by the security plugin.

children.label: getState
description: This function returns the current state of anonymous access.

children.label: getCapabilities
description: This function returns the capabilities of the anonymous access user.

interfaces.label: AnonymousAccessState
description: The state of anonymous access.

children.label: isEnabled
description: Whether anonymous access is enabled or not.

children.label: accessURLParameters
description:
If anonymous access is enabled, this reflects what URL parameters need to be added to a Kibana link to make it publicly accessible.
Note that if anonymous access is the only authentication method, this will be null.
